parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel without warning, leading to unexpected stalls, accidents, and stranded drivers.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads incorrectly
shows full or half-full when the tank is empty
or fluctuates erratically. The vehicle may stall or shut off while driving
and the "Service Engine Soon" light may appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially if it occurs on a highway or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
often without warning
and may be accompanied by a loss of power steering and other systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the fuel gauge and other essential systems to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The instrument cluster fails to display accurate information
including fuel level
speed
and other vital systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Failure to Restart
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The failure to restart the engine can lead to further safety risks.
symptoms: The engine stalls suddenly
often without warning
while driving at various speeds. The vehicle may not restart immediately
or may require multiple attempts to start. The check engine light may illuminate
and the vehicle may experience a burning smell or heat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Crankshaft and Camshaft Position Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft and camshaft position sensors can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls suddenly
often without warning
while driving at various speeds. The check engine light may illuminate
and the vehicle may experience difficulty starting or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to engine damage and potentially cause accidents due to engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of engine oil
often requiring frequent oil changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Crankshaft and Camshaft Position Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft and camshaft position sensors can cause the engine to stall or shut off without warning, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle experiences reduced engine power
the vehicle is difficult to start or will not start at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not show the correct amount of fuel
the vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly
the service engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, potentially causing engine failure and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of engine oil
carbon buildup in the combustion chambers.
